# dataset/ — raw source dataset (NOT in git)

This folder is kept in the repo, but its contents are **git-ignored** because the files are
large (~440 MB total) and binary-ish. Git only tracks this `.gitkeep` placeholder.

## What goes here

Download the dataset files from Google Drive and drop them directly into this `dataset/` folder:

Expected files (run: `mecca-pkg-llm/dataset/`):

| File                | Size    | What it is                                                        |
|---------------------|---------|-------------------------------------------------------------------|
| `products.jsonl`    | ~212 MB | 49,881 lipstick products (nested product + PP/SP/TP packaging BOM) |
| `material_view.csv` | ~225 MB | 676,181 flattened per-material rows (one row per material entry)   |
| `batch_job.json`    | ~8 MB   | Original generation batch job record                              |
| `manifest.json`     | ~1 KB   | Run metadata (run_id, target=Lipstick, stats, file map)           |

## Why it's needed

`scripts/01_extract_chunk.py` reads `dataset/products.jsonl` as the entry point of the whole
pipeline (see RUNBOOK step 1). Without these files the data-prep steps cannot run — but if you
are only **deploying / using an already-trained model** (RUNBOOK step 5), you do NOT need them.

After copying the files in, verify:

    ls -lh dataset/        # should show the 4 files above
    wc -l dataset/products.jsonl   # expect 49881 lines
